reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Assembly is a challenge
reviews.reviewText: First.. you generally get what you pay for and this set was quite inexpensive… something that will be used only on occasion so I didn’t want to spend much for items. Fair enough. Seems sturdy once assembled. That may take some time since not everything is aligned and the work area is a bit awkward. But it can be done A hammer comes in handy to set the back and sides. I finally found a bit to match the Allen wrench and use in my multi bit screwdriver. I highly recommend using one. So all things considered, a decent buy for the use. I’ll see how it holds up to the weather.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Learn your tolerance and patience levels!
reviews.reviewText: Assembly seemed straight forward. It is not. Many holes were covered by the plastic I had to cut away to even find the screw hole. The bolts were difficult as all get out to put in most of the holes. The glass for the table is maybe good in theory but superfluous and the suction cups on the table top were so wonky, from shipping I guess, it isn’t exactly tethered very well either. If you’re looking to curse, argue with yourself, and question your own sanity - this is a great patio set for you. I went through all stages of grief putting it together. After all was said and done (2 hours btw) I’m just glad it’s over with. I’ve assembled many pieces of furniture in my day but this one really was something special. The chairs size and comfort seem adequate. Are they sturdy though? I guess. Some bolts never truly felt “I can’t turn this bolt another turn” tight and some were tight but kept turning even after it didn’t make sense to be possible to keep turning. The padding isn’t exactly thick but it’s sufficient. I can’t say I’d recommend buying this, unless you’re really up for a challenge. The price is right on the set for how they look, but it’s in my ‘never again’ category. A freak windstorm could launch these off my patio and I would not buy it again. Well, maybe pre assembled… they are decent looking.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy Outdoor Furniture
reviews.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised at how sturdy this little patio set is. It is a little challenging to put together alone (two people to hold things in place are better), but the assembled product is great.

Arrived in time but a pain to put together. Instructions I received was for a different model. So I had to put it together without a guide and it turns out, the sockets don’t fit into each other properly. I saw this on a few other reviews and figured it was an isolated case but same happened to me. 1 chair was an easy setup, the other is poorly made and doesn’t fit together at all. Hoping the seller sends me a replacement or a refund. Not happy with this purchase.
